# Admin Authentication

The admin console is gated by JWT session cookies with CSRF double-submit and a
5-minute MFA freshness window for super-admin mutations. **Legacy `X-Admin-Key`
and the `ADMIN_AUTH_ENABLED` feature flag were retired** in Phase 6g/6h; they no
longer exist in code. Any new admin endpoint or admin UI that sneaks them back
in is wrong.

## Backend dependency chain

Declared in `backend/src/agent_service/api/admin_auth.py`:

- `require_admin` — valid JWT access cookie + `admin` role. 401 on missing/invalid token, 403 on role mismatch.
- `require_super_admin` — chains on `require_admin` + `super_admin` role.
- `require_mfa_fresh` — chains on `require_super_admin` + `mfa_verified_at` within `JWT_MFA_FRESHNESS_SECONDS` (default 300 s).

Every admin endpoint must `Depends(require_admin)` at minimum. Super-admin
mutations (KB writes, settings changes) must `Depends(require_mfa_fresh)` so the
5-min MFA window is enforced server-side — never at the frontend only.

Error payload shape (matches RFC 7807 Problem Details partially):

```json
{"detail": {"code": "<snake_case_code>", "operation": "<endpoint_name>", "message": "<human_readable>"}}
```

Codes: `no_session`, `token_expired`, `invalid_token`, `not_admin`, `not_super_admin`, `mfa_required`, `invalid_credentials`, `csrf_missing`, `csrf_invalid`.

## CSRF double-submit

State-changing admin endpoints (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE under `/admin/auth/mfa/verify`,
`/admin/auth/refresh`, `/admin/auth/logout`, and anything wrapped by the super-admin
deps above) declare `dependencies=[Depends(require_csrf_token)]`.

- Cookie name: `mft_admin_csrf` (non-httpOnly so JS can read)
- Header name: `X-CSRF-Token` (frontend echoes the cookie into this header)
- Comparison: `hmac.compare_digest` (constant-time)

Frontend handling lives in `shared/api/http.ts` — `STATE_CHANGING_METHODS` set
must include every method that can mutate (`POST`, `PUT`, `PATCH`, `DELETE`).
Missing methods silently drop CSRF and break the endpoint.

## Cookie flags

- `mft_admin_at` (access token) — `httpOnly` + `Secure` + `SameSite=Strict` + path `/`
- `mft_admin_rt` (refresh token) — same flags, path scoped to `/admin/auth/refresh`
- `mft_admin_csrf` — non-httpOnly (JS reads), `Secure` + `SameSite=Strict`

The `Secure` flag is controlled by `ADMIN_AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE` (default `true`);
set `false` only for local HTTP dev. Never in production.

## Frontend convention — mutations MUST use `withMfa`

Any frontend call that hits an endpoint protected by `require_mfa_fresh` must
route through `useMfaPrompt().withMfa(label, () => apiCall())`. This wraps the
call in an `ApiError(403, detail.code='mfa_required')` catch, opens the TOTP
modal, and retries on success. Skipping this wrapper means the user gets a
plain error toast with no way to proceed.

```ts
// ✅ Correct
const { withMfa } = useMfaPrompt()
const deleteMut = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (row) => withMfa('delete this FAQ', () => deleteFaq(row.id)),
  onError: (err) => {
    if (err instanceof MfaCancelled) return // silent cancel
    toast.error(getErrorMessage(err))
  },
})

// ❌ Wrong — 403 mfa_required shows as a plain toast, user is stuck
const deleteMut = useMutation({
  mutationFn: (row) => deleteFaq(row.id),
  onError: (err) => toast.error(getErrorMessage(err)),
})
```

`MfaCancelled` (exported from `MfaPromptProvider`) is thrown when the user
dismisses the TOTP modal. Error handlers should branch on it to suppress the
toast (silent cancel) — the user deliberately backed out, no error to show.

## Enrollment

Single super-admin setup via `backend/scripts/enroll_super_admin.py`. See
`docs/runbooks/super-admin-enrollment.md` for the step-by-step runbook
including the **`$$`-escape trap** in docker-compose env_files (argon2 hashes
contain `$` characters that compose will silently consume unless escaped).

For lockout recovery, see `docs/runbooks/admin_auth_mfa_recovery.md`.

## Required env vars

All five are required for the backend to boot (fail-closed validation in
`core/config.py::_validate_admin_auth_config`):

- `JWT_SECRET` — ≥32 bytes (RFC 7518 §3.2); HS256 only
- `FERNET_MASTER_KEY` — Fernet-generated key for TOTP-secret at-rest encryption
- `SUPER_ADMIN_EMAIL` — the `sub` claim; typed at login
- `SUPER_ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH` — argon2id; `$`-characters must be `$$`-escaped in .env
- `SUPER_ADMIN_TOTP_SECRET_ENC` — Fernet-encrypted base32 TOTP secret

Optional overrides (documented in `.env.example` under Admin Authentication):
`JWT_ALGORITHM` (HS256/HS384/HS512 only — allowlisted at module load),
`JWT_ISSUER`, `JWT_AUDIENCE`, `JWT_ACCESS_TTL_SECONDS`,
`JWT_REFRESH_TTL_SECONDS`, `JWT_MFA_FRESHNESS_SECONDS`,
`ADMIN_AUTH_COOKIE_SECURE`, `ADMIN_AUTH_COOKIE_NAME_ACCESS`,
`ADMIN_AUTH_COOKIE_NAME_REFRESH`.

## Rate limits

Enforced by `RedisRateLimiter` (fail_closed default):

- `POST /admin/auth/login` — 5 req/min per IP
- `POST /admin/auth/mfa/verify` — 5 req/min per IP

Login path is also subject to the 5-strike TOTP lockout (`admin_totp.py`): 5
consecutive failed TOTP attempts across any time window triggers a 15-min
absolute lockout via a Redis marker at `admin_auth:locked:<sub>`. Recovery via
`docs/runbooks/admin_auth_mfa_recovery.md` Option B.

## Testing

Backend endpoint tests use `httpx.ASGITransport` + `AsyncClient` +
`fakeredis.aioredis.FakeRedis(decode_responses=True)` — see
`backend/tests/test_admin_auth_endpoints.py` for the pattern. Frontend
`MfaPromptProvider` tests use `vi.hoisted()` for mock classes (see lesson L6 in
`tasks/lessons.md`) and mock `@/shared/api/http` at module level.

When adding a new admin endpoint that chains `require_mfa_fresh`, add a paired
test case that asserts 403 with `detail.code === "mfa_required"` when the JWT
is MFA-stale. This is the contract frontend `withMfa` depends on.
